Defendant Lorraine Wilks in court with Attorney Cord Williams Klein.  Catelin Ringersma appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Matter here for a Deferred Prosecution Agreement Hearing.    The parties have agreed to a deferred judgment agreement.The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, pled GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionaire/Wiaver of Rights and Addendum to Plea Questionaire received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty but WITHHELD entry of Judgement of Conviction.  The Court reviewed the Intake Requirement and Further Conditions with the defendant.  The court approved the Deferred Prosecution Agreement and ordered the proceedings suspended for a period of six months.  Matter set for a review hearing on May 17, 2016 at 8:30am in Br. 33, Judge Ashley's court.
